01:05:44.000 --> 01:06:03.000
So, the strategy of the upper level has been developed. What's next? Next, our task is to decompose the strategy according to the hierarchy of the organizational company.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:38.000
The organization structure of the company is used to carry out this process. The process of vertical and horizontal decomposition is highlighted.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:57.000
At the vertical level, we transfer some of the goals and indicators from the company level to the level of individual business units or departments.

01:06:57.000 --> 01:07:20.000
Further, at the level of individual business units, the same transfer is carried out at the level of each employee.

01:07:50.000 --> 01:08:02.000
Why is this necessary? This is necessary so that when the strategy is implemented, our units do not start acting according to the principle of swan, cock and pike.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:39.000
Let's look at the problem of vertical decomposition.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:59.000
Vertical decomposition is necessary in order to transfer the goals of the unit from the level of the higher management through the middle management link to the level of line managers and line employees.

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:16.000
And then to get feedback in the form of indicators and achievements of the target values of the indicators. This feedback will go from line employees through the middle management link to the higher management.

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:35.000
The methods of vertical decomposition of the strategic map can be different. As a rule, at least three methods of six existing methods are used.

01:09:35.000 --> 01:10:00.000
The first method is the method of vertical decomposition.

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:23.000
The second method is the method of vertical decomposition.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:34.000
In this case, we look at the strategic map of the upper level and independently formulate our own goals that will be included in the strategy of our unit.

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:38.000
The only thing we need is for these things to somehow combine.

01:10:38.000 --> 01:10:46.000
The next method is the direct determination of goals based on the goals of the upper level.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:11:03.000
We take the goals of the upper level, which are developed by the company, and transfer them to the strategic map of this unit.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:12.000
Naturally, we change the goals of the upper level in case we have a specific activity.

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:18.000
The next method is the method of adaptation of target indicators from strategic events.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:35.000
We take the goals, target indicators, strategic events that are included in the strategic map of the upper level and adapt them to what our unit is doing.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:51.000
That is, we take not the whole value of the indicator, but only part of it.

01:11:51.000 --> 01:12:02.000
Not all strategic events can be carried out at our level.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:07.000
The next method is the method of combining standard individual goals.

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:23.000
We can take part of the goals from the strategic map of the upper level, but we will have to come up with part of it ourselves, depending on what specific activity is laid down in our functional zone, in our unit.

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:29.000
The next method is the method of direct determination of strategic events.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:47.000
We look at the goals of the company, at the events that the company intends to carry out, and we just formulate the events that our unit can carry out.

01:12:48.000 --> 01:13:03.000
And finally, the method of open communication, when communication is carried out within the framework of meetings, within the framework of work of working groups, regarding the development of strategic maps of the units.

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:14.000
Only in this case, each unit goes through the entire path of development of the strategy, all the stages that we are now going through in this topic.

01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:19.000
Then comes the implementation.

01:13:19.000 --> 01:13:38.000
In order to implement the developed strategy, including goals, events, indicators, target values, as component parts, we need to develop an implementation plan.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:47.000
We need to distribute the responsibility zones for the achievement of the event.

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:58.000
We need to determine the calendar plan for the implementation of the event, i.e. the date of the beginning and the date of the end of each event.

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:02.000
We need to consolidate the centers of responsibility, i.e. the executors.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:07.000
We need to consolidate the centers of control, i.e. who controls the execution.

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:14.000
As a rule, the centers of responsibility and the centers of control are assigned in accordance with the organizational structure of the company.

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:24.000
And finally, we need to assign the target indicators of how we will carry out this event.

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:33.000
We need to understand that the event is carried out based on the value of this indicator.

01:14:33.000 --> 01:14:37.000
The implementation of the strategy is a continuous process.

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:44.000
It is a continuous process of transforming the strategic plan of the company into continuous actions, and then into achievements.

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:53.000
Therefore, the process of developing and implementing the strategy will be closed.

01:14:53.000 --> 01:15:04.000
Starting with the diagnosis, planning, then execution, then checking the results and carrying out control and monitoring events,

01:15:04.000 --> 01:15:09.000
then, based on the analysis plan, controlling the changes.

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:17.000
As I said, this process is cyclical, non-stop.

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:22.000
Thus, we have developed a strategy.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:28.000
