01:40:40.000 --> 01:40:48.000
Increasing the value for shareholders at the expense of maximizing the flows of free money is the final financial goal of the company.

01:40:48.000 --> 01:40:59.000
This is motivated by the statements of external studies that showed a correlation between free money flows and the increase in the share price.

01:40:59.000 --> 01:41:10.000
Further, the growth of profitability and profitability is an expansion of the existing business, which means an increase in income only after the increase in profitability.

01:41:11.000 --> 01:41:20.000
In the area of management of costs, the company was to reduce trade and general administrative costs in order to increase operating profits.

01:41:20.000 --> 01:41:36.000
The next goal is capital optimization. The company needed to effectively manage its physical and financial capital so that the growth of income and profits contributed to increasing the value for shareholders.

01:41:37.000 --> 01:41:55.000
Finally, the company's growth is due to strategic transactions, that is, the creation of new strategic partners that would facilitate the development of the company's key competencies, product management in this category and the construction of a distribution system.

01:41:56.000 --> 01:42:01.000
The next step was to analyze the interested groups.

